Course Summary

This Saxon Algebra 1 Homeschool: Textbook Companion Course uses simple and fun videos to help study algebra for an exam and earn a better grade. Each of the lessons is about five minutes long and is sequenced to align with the chapters in the Saxon Algebra 1 Homeschool textbook.

Who's It For?

Anyone enrolled using the Saxon Algebra 1 Homeschool textbook should consider this companion course. You will learn the material faster, retain it longer and earn a better grade.

How It Works

  • Identify the chapter in your Saxon Algebra 1 Homeschool textbook with which you need help.
  • Find the corresponding chapter within our Saxon Algebra 1 Homeschool Textbook Companion Course.
  • Watch fun videos that cover the algebra topics you need to learn or review.
  • Complete the quizzes to test your understanding.
  • If you need additional help, re-watch the videos until you've mastered the material or submit a question for one of our instructors.

Why It Works

  • Fun Content: These videos make learning Saxon Algebra 1 fun with engaging animation and real-world examples.
  • Great Instructors: Study.com uses exceptional educators who can take concepts like calculating square and cube roots and make them easy to understand.
  • Multiple Ways to Learn: Watch videos or read the lesson transcript.
  • Easy to Use: Access this textbook companion on any smartphone, tablet or laptop.

Course Topics

Students will be able to learn all the algebra topics in the textbook with this engaging course, including:

  • Whole numbers, fractions and decimals
  • Sets and coordinate graphing
  • Number theory and real numbers
  • Measurement and conversions
  • Proportions, ratios, rates and percentages
  • Exponents and roots
  • Statistics and probability
  • Expressions, equations and functions
  • Lines and plane figures
  • Solid figures
  • Area, perimeter, circumference, surface area and volume
